						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Āṅgira</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the perpetual obeisance of Tiruvēṅgaḍa Kōnamma, who is said to have attained union with the lord <hi rend="italic">(Sāyujya) i.e.,</hi> died, when the deity and the goddess were getting down the western steps of the Raṅga-maṇḍapa and taking a turn to the north in the month of <hi rend="bold">Dhanus in the year Āṅgira.</hi> In characters of of the 16th century A.D. The year <hi rend="bold">Āṅgira</hi> falling in this period may correspond to <hi rend="bold">1512 or 1572 A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
